  "texts": [
    "However, these conclusions mainly extend to medium-sized datasets.TabZilla (McElfresh et al, 2023) conducted the most comprehensive large-scale study against 19 machine learning, deep learning (Gorishniy et al, 2021), and SSL4NS-TD algorithms (Somepalli et al, 2022; Arik and Pfister, 2021; Yoon et al, 2020; Hollmann et al, 2023) across 176 classification tabular datasets, and provided a benchmark of the 36 hardest datasets with 300 to 1,000,000 samples.",
    "Tabzilla uncovered none of the existing approaches perform well on all datasets.",
    "Particularly, transformer-based SSL4NS-TD algorithms (Arik and Pfister, 2021) perform well on larger datasets while PFN SSL4NS-TD algorithms (Hollmann et al, 2023) perform well on smaller datasets.",
    "XGBoost (Chen and Guestrin, 2016) performs well on datasets with many irregular features.",
    "Among SSL4NS-TD algorithms, TabPFN (Hollmann et al, 2023) performs particularly well across the benchmark, definitively outperforming tree-based models with less than 1,250 samples."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}